Package com.hedera.sdk.common

Class HederaKeySignatureThreshold

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hedera.sdk.common.HederaKeySignatureThreshold
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class HederaKeySignatureThreshold
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class is a helper for managing keys and signatures in tandem. Each instance of the object stores a threshold and List of HederaKeySignature

      • setSignatureForKey

        public boolean setSignatureForKey​(byte[] key,
                                  byte[] signature,
                                  boolean stopAtFirst)
        Sets the signatures against a matching key If they key is found but has signature already set, looks for another matching key If stopAtFirst is true, only the first matching key with no signature is set otherwise all matching keys with no signature are set
        Parameters:
        key - the key to look for
        signature - the signature value to set
        stopAtFirst - sets only the first matching key with empty signature if true
        Returns:
        boolean true if a signature was set

      • setSignatureForKeys

        public boolean setSignatureForKeys​(byte[][] keys,
                                   byte[][] signatures,
                                   boolean stopAtFirst)
        Sets the signatures against matching keys If a key is found but has signature already set, looks for another matching key If stopAtFirst is true, only the first matching key with no signature is set otherwise all matching keys with no signature are set
        Parameters:
        keys - a byte[][] array of keys to look for
        signatures - a byte[][] array of signatures for the keys
        stopAtFirst - sets only the first matching key with empty signature if true
        Returns:
        boolean true if a signature was set
